# definitions.json (optional)

This repo previously mounted `definitions.json` into RabbitMQ. That file contained a
hard-coded password hash for `guest` that did **not** match `guest`/`guest`, which
caused `ACCESS_REFUSED` / invalid credentials when Spring apps connected.

Topology is created by **Spring Cloud Stream** at runtime, so no broker-side
definitions import is required for this POC.

If you need pre-declared exchanges/queues later, export definitions from a healthy
broker and mount them — ensure user passwords match `${RABBITMQ_USER}` /
`${RABBITMQ_PASSWORD}` or omit `users` from the export.
